    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i've seen some people say that the UN is basically just a tool for the big powers to do whatever they want and that it has no real legitimacy anymore because of that. do historians actually consider the idea that the UN is fundamentally broken/obsolete to be a mainstream view, or is that more of a fringe argument?",
